Title: Object: Sepulchral chambers near Bethany
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 18 in volume II: a group of men with turbans in a chamber with an arched roof, two at top of steps on the left, some descending another steps on the right which leads to another chamber below, a man in the centre holding a torch; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.II.18)
